The paper deals with the problem of finding the longest systematic-length for a linear minimum storage regenerating code, which involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT), linear algebra (cs.DS), distributed computing (cs.DC), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of geometric analysis, which is a common technique in signal processing and machine learning (cs.SI).
